HEADWORD: Dakir
<hw>Da"kir</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Dicker</er>.]</ety> <fld>(O. Eng. &
Scots Law)</fld> <def>A measure of certain commodities by number,
usually ten or twelve, but sometimes twenty; <as>as, a <ex>daker</ex> of
hides consisted of ten skins; a <ex>daker</ex> of gloves of ten
pairs.</as></def> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
